properties.title: Oliver's Spring
properties.description: Two Gypsy Hearts posted a photo: Columbia Center // Downtown // Seattle, Washington Today was Oliver's first day out on a harness and leash. It was also his first time interacting with strangers and other dogs. He did very well and are really proud of him.Video: Oliver's First Adventure ~*~ On Tuesday May 3rd, we adopted an 11 week old Boston Terrier & Dachshund mix from a family that loved him but could no longer keep him. He came into our lives unexpectedly today, though we were seeking to adopt a dog for a long time. The minute we saw his face we knew he was an Oliver Berthold. I find that he exhibits Boston Terrier personality traits moreso than Dachshund traits. He made himself at home right away, however there will be quite the long road ahead in training him and establishing the Alpha role. Oliver is very intelligent and already knows his name, so I can already tell that he will be good in training. He is a real sweetheart, loveable, and just wants to play with everyone (including the cats) all the time. Chloe and Luca still haven't warmed up to him yet, but I'm guessing that Luca will be the first to. We are so excited to start this new chapter in our life. Oliver is adjusting fantastically to our household. He is already so loyal to us and is training so well. The cats are still adjusting and it will probably be another week or two before we can do one on one training by introducing him to Oliver while he is on the leash. © Two Gypsy Hearts(photo taken by Kate)

properties.title: Oliver | American La France
properties.description: two gypsy hearts posted a photo: ~* Historic Pioneer Square Fire Festival *~ We wandered into this event at random (right down the street from where we live), and am so glad we did. My father was a firefighter, and I have tremendous respect for them and the work they do. I grew up going to firehouses and spending time in them. We also got to talk with people in the industry and visited the museum.Occidental Park // Pioneer Square // Seattle, Washington "The historic Pioneer Historic Pioneer Square Fire Festival will be held this Saturday, July 9 from 11:00 am to 5:00 pm in Occidental Park. The Fire Festival celebrates the rebirth of Pioneer Square after the Great Seattle Fire of June 6, 1889. The fire destroyed 120 acres or 25 city blocks and caused an estimated $20 million in damage. It was the most devastating fire ever to hit Seattle and led to the birth of the modern day Seattle Fire Department. The festival gives a glimpse into Seattle’s past. Displays include antique and classic fire engines, classic police cars, a gold mining demonstration, and other family friendly activities. Kids can color pictures while sitting in the back of a 1940 fire engine, or try on firefighter turnout gear. Located one to two blocks away from Occidental Square Park are: the Last Resort Fire Department Museum, located in Seattle Fire Department Headquarters; the Seattle Metropolitan Police Museum located in a historic building; and the Klondike Gold Rush National Historical Park – Seattle, located in the restored Cadillac Hotel. All three museums have activities for kids, and they will be open and free to the public on the day of the Fire Festival." More info here and here.

properties.title: Connie, Sierra, Oliver, & Jen
properties.description: two gypsy hearts posted a photo: ~* Historic Pioneer Square Fire Festival *~ We wandered into this event at random (right down the street from where we live), and am so glad we did. My father was a firefighter, and I have tremendous respect for them and the work they do. I grew up going to firehouses and spending time in them. We also got to talk with people in the industry and visited the museum. We encountered and befriended a lady named Connie and her miniature long-haired Dachshund, Sierra.
